# Compiled binaries
/akari
/akari.exe
*.exe
*.test

# Test and coverage output
*.out
coverage.*

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# templ-generated Go. The .templ files are the source of truth; `templ generate`
# (run via `go generate ./...` in CI, Docker, and `make build`) writes these on
# every build, so they are not committed. Keeping them out of the tree is also
# why a plain `go build` never reports a "-dirty" version from codegen.
internal/server/web/*_templ.go

# Editor and OS cruft
.DS_Store
*.swp

# Local Claude Code agent worktree state. Shared agent config under .claude/
# (such as .claude/skills/) is committed; this per-machine scratch state is not.
/.claude/worktrees/
